<TEXT>
the first man since the vietnam war to get 
through eight years of draft eligibility without being called to 
arms said something was missing from his 26th birthday celebration 
im proud within myself about it i wish i had an award or 
something though that would have been nice maybe a plaque to hang 
on the wall said joseph frank 
frank the first 18yearold to sign up and be processed by the 
selective service system after draft registration was revived in 
1981 turned 26 on friday that made him too old to be called up 
even if congress and the president reactivate the draft according 
to selective service officials in washington 
i didnt have to go active and im glad about that frank 
said but if it was gods will i would have gone its a blessing 
to be a soldier for this country 
frank said he had no idea he was the first man in the country to 
register when he did so he said he just followed the law and signed 
up 
i wasnt worried about being drafted when i was 18 i dont 
think i even thought about it but if it had happened it would have 
just happened when i turned 21 i got more worried about it frank 
said 
the draft was stopped in 1973 after the end of the vietnam war 
but registration was revived on jan 5 1981 federal law requires 
every man to register with selective service within 30 days of his 
18th birthday 
</TEXT>
