afghanistan to help defend the government from moslem guerrilla 
attacks 
in the last few years the party has sought to distance itself 
publicly from its marxist beginnings but the moslem resistance 
movement composed of seven pakistanbased parties and eight 
iranbased parties routinely refers to the party as godless 
communists 
zahir shah is increasingly mentioned as the only afghan leader 
with sufficient stature to serve as even a symbolic leader 
vorontsov met resistance leaders in saudi arabia on dec 3 
giving the guerrillas the kremlins first public recognition as a 
negotiating force for afghanistans future 
the guerrillas have been fighting kabuls government since the 
1978 coup with arms supplied by the united states pakistan china 
and several arab nations the guerrillas also attacked soviet forces 
that numbered 115000 a year ago 
the soviets started withdrawing troops last may under a 
unsponsored accord signed in geneva the remaining 50000 red 
army soldiers are scheduled to leave afghanistan by feb 15 under 
the accord 
kawyani in his late 30s with a black mustache reminiscent of 
josef stalin accused the united states and pakistan of violating 
the geneva accord by continuing to arm the guerrillas 
he demanded pakistan stop providing shelter for the guerrillas 
the seven mujahedeen parties based in pakistan openly maintain 
offices in peshawar 20 miles from the afghan border 
