<TEXT>
a predawn earthquake jolted the swiss 
alps today but no major damage was reported authorities said 
switzerlands strongest tremor in five years which measured 38 
on the richter scale was felt mainly in the region around the 
valais alps ski resort of cransmontana the swiss federal 
polytechnical institute in zurich reported 
tremors were felt up to 30 miles from the quakes epicenter said 
the institutes chief earthquake specialist dietermayer rosa 
he said one resident called authorities to report a crack in a 
house wall 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph every increase of one number means that the ground 
motion is 10 times greater 
an earthquake of magnitude 2 is the smallest normally felt by 
humans while a quake of magnitude 4 can cause moderate damage in 
populated areas 
a tremor of magnitude 7 is considered a major earthquake capable 
of widespread heavy damage in populated areas 
