still favor the nearbuy months said bob baker an analyst with 
prudentialbache securities inc so confidence erodes as the 
months go out 
the 13member cartel agreed late last year to cut back production 
to 185 million barrels a day starting jan 1 from over 22 million 
barrels a day a worldwide oversupply of oil has kept crude prices 
weak 
